I was able to solve my issue, as I suspected my `amplifyconfiguration.json` was missing some fields. This is my working config:

```
{
  "auth": {
    "plugins": {
      "awsCognitoAuthPlugin": {
        "IdentityManager": {
          "Default": {}
        },
        "CognitoUserPool": {
          "Default": {
            "PoolId": "[POOL ID]",
            "AppClientId": "[APP CLIENT ID]",
            "AppClientSecret": "[APP CLIENT SECRET]",
            "Region": "[REGION]"
          }
        },
        "Auth": {
          "Default": {
            "authenticationFlowType": "USER_SRP_AUTH",
            "OAuth": {
              "WebDomain": "[ENV]-[APP NAME].auth.[REGION].amazoncognito.com",
              "TokenURI": "https://[ENV]-[APP NAME].auth.[REGION].amazoncognito.com/oauth2/token",
              "SignInURI": "https://[ENV]-[APP NAME].auth.[REGION].amazoncognito.com/oauth2/authorize",
              "AppClientId": "[CLIENT ID]",
              "AppClientSecret": "[APP CLIENT SECRET]",
              "SignInRedirectURI": "myapp://",
              "SignOutRedirectURI": "myapp://",
              "Scopes": [
                "email",
                "openid"
              ],
              "ResponseType": "code"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The added fields being `TokenURI`, `SignInURI`,  and `AppClientSecret` to the `OAuth` section. 

I was only able to find my needed fields through what seems to be older documentation: [https://docs.amplify.aws/sdk/auth/hosted-ui/q/platform/ios/#signing-out-via-the-hosted-ui](url)

I think it would be very helpful if the template provided in the newer documentation either included these fields or mentioned them:
[https://docs.amplify.aws/lib/auth/getting-started/q/platform/ios/#set-up-backend-resources](url)

Lastly, while I see many social providers mentioned, I did not see any mention of SAML providers in the below page which I think would useful as I began to doubt whether I was using the right api call which the older documentation mentions above:

[https://docs.amplify.aws/lib/auth/social/q/platform/ios/](url)
